This paper presents a novel method for learning reward functions in reinforcement learning, which is a core topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the theoretical results of maximizing the objective function, which relates to optimization and control, suggesting cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper's empirical evaluation involves various domains, including Atari games and robotics, indicating cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as another possible sub-category.
